name: Saad Hamid
text: Here is why the 3-point pitch works (1) You force your brain to make your pitch concise (2) Listeners are able to remember what you said (3) Communication flow becomes easy and simple As I said, the 3-point pitch works you see what I did there.

name: Saad Hamid
text: You can do wonders with the power of 3 There is a good chance you are pitching something all the time, personally of professionally, to your partner or to your boss, to your investor or to your parents. Limiting your pitch to main 3 points can make it effective.

name: Saad Hamid
text: At the same time I also think this is one of the areas open for disruption. Imagine all things we could do if we could somehow offload our brain to a cookie and still use it while we sleep? That way we can make 2/3 of our life productive that is now wasted in sleep.

name: Saad Hamid
text: If I had a superpower it would be my sleep. One thing I have never compromised on in my 10 years of professional life is my sleep and daily I manage to get at least 7-8 hours of uninterrupted sleep. Good sleep can reduce stress, improve memory and keeps you in a good mood.

name: Saad Hamid
text: @Nash During our @Acumen fellowship we used to call these problems as adaptive challenges' and what baffles me is how most Pakistani founders fail to recognise the people challenges and just focus on building the next big app or platform without taking into account market or policy.

name: Saad Hamid
text: I personally find so much joy in fighting such challenges or problems where you have to manage complex relationships and bring various stakeholders in alignment with one common goal despite their values, loyalties and losses. There should be a name for such kind of joy.

name: Saad Hamid
text: Technical problems are so overrated. The best problems to solve are people problems where you have to really dig deep into the situation, analyse it from multiple lenses, identify key players and then come up with a common minimum' agreement between all parties.

name: Saad Hamid
text: More power to #AuratMarch and the women of Pakistan and much more power to men who, despite being bashed for whatever concerns they show, still show up for women every day.

name: Saad Hamid
text: I was planning not to say it out publicly because I know I will get heat but I just couldn't keep it inside. #AuratMarch is about men as much as it is about women, it's a public planet partnership and no movement can be successful by alienating one side.

name: Saad Hamid
text: This conflict is perhaps more because I am a dad but more importantly #AuratMarch matters to me because it defines so much of what my family's future looks like - a family that is more female than male.

name: Saad Hamid
text: Me voicing my thoughts has further grown the conflict, specially after what people have said to me, and here I am looking at my 5 yo daughter who means the world to me and thinking How do I not get a say at what her future looks like?'

name: Saad Hamid
text: I am lucky to have female friends from across a spectrum, from the most liberal to the conservative, and I have reached out to ask them if I as a man' get a say at this, or even as someone who has females around him who are voicing their unpopular opinions to him

name: Saad Hamid
text: I have already received a lot of heat for voicing these thoughts, from one side of the group, in a space that I thought I could call a safe space.

name: Saad Hamid
text: I love #AuratMarch and the movement but I feel conflicted about using hard language on posters, specially as dad of a 5 yo female.
